<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,976,194,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,411,327,349]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis. Pterothorax:</emphasis>
Scutellum with posterior apex pointed (Fig. 3); elytra with apices not upturned (
<figureCitation box="[413,489,354,376]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[167,206,1430,1449]" captionTargetBox="[149,973,194,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[149,973,194,1408]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–16. Dorsal habitus of Blaiseus spp. 8) B. bedeli Fleutiaux; 9) B. chiapasensis new species; 10) B. daklakensis new species; 11) B. daklakensis new species, side view; 12) B. malayensis new species; 13) B. mexicanus new species; 14) B. nothoafricanus new species; 15) B. zamoranoensis new species female; 16) B. zamoranoensis new species female, side view. Scale bar 5 1.0 mm. All photos are dorsal view of male specimens unless specified otherwise." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5496090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5496090/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[507,561,354,376]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Legs:</emphasis>
Femora and tibiae expanded (fossorial); protibiae with posterior tooth at apex but not at midlength. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[815,917,381,403]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Free portion of median lobe convex laterally in dorsal profile (
<figureCitation box="[745,823,407,429]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[196,235,1249,1268]" captionTargetBox="[188,994,194,1226]" captionTargetId="figure-60@5.[186,994,194,1226]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 17–26. Dorsal view of aedeagi of Blaiseus spp. 17) B. bedeli Fleutiaux; 18) B. chiapasensis new species; 19) B. daklakensis new species; 20) B. fujianus new species; 21) B. guatemalensis new species; 22) B. laoensis new species; 23) B. malayensis new species; 24) B. mexicanus new species; 25) B. nothoafricanus new species; 26) B. zamoranoensis new species. d 5 dorsal apex of parameres; i 5 inner apex; v 5 ventral apex. Scale bar 5 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5496093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5496093/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="94" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,976,194,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,361,434,456]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Description. Male:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[457,539,434,456]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="94" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
. Integument red-brown to brown, elytra with basal half of intervals 2–4 and all of intervals 8–9 darker than rest; habitus like 
<taxonomicName box="[198,350,488,509]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Blaiseus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daklakensis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[198,350,488,509]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">B. daklakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[365,490,487,509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[513,586,487,509]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[167,206,1430,1449]" captionTargetBox="[149,973,194,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[149,973,194,1408]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–16. Dorsal habitus of Blaiseus spp. 8) B. bedeli Fleutiaux; 9) B. chiapasensis new species; 10) B. daklakensis new species; 11) B. daklakensis new species, side view; 12) B. malayensis new species; 13) B. mexicanus new species; 14) B. nothoafricanus new species; 15) B. zamoranoensis new species female; 16) B. zamoranoensis new species female, side view. Scale bar 5 1.0 mm. All photos are dorsal view of male specimens unless specified otherwise." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5496090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5496090/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,669,487,509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Head:</emphasis>
Antennae reaching beyond mesocoxae; labrum not convex in side view, nasale with ovoid pits antero-mesad of antennal fossae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[345,455,540,562]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Prothorax:</emphasis>
Posterior edge of pronotum with 2 apices mesally; hypomeron with hind edge sinuate immediately meso-ventrad of hind angles (
<figureCitation box="[154,214,594,616]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[167,206,1083,1102]" captionTargetBox="[151,970,194,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-118@2.[151,970,194,1061]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–2. Lateral view of pronotum of Blaiseus spp. 1) B. malayensis new species; 2) B. nothoafricanus new species. Arrows indicate concavity of hypomeron immediately mesoventrad of hind angles. Scale bar 5 1 mm. Figs. 3–4. Dorsal view of scutellum of Blaiseus spp. 3) B. mexicanus new species; 4) B. bedeli Fleutiaux. Scale bar 5 1 mm. Figs. 5– 6. Dorsal view of protibia of Blaiseus spp. 5) B. mexicanus new species; 6) B. guatemalensis new species. m 5 tooth at midlength; a 5 apical tooth. Scale bar 5 1 mm. Fig. 7. Wing of Blaiseus bedeli Fleutiaux. Arrows indicate forked vein CuA1. Scale bar 5 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5496088" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5496088/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Prosternum with ventral surface of prosternal process surface weakly carinate laterally. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[338,466,620,642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Pterothorax:</emphasis>
Scutellum with posterior apex pointed (Fig. 3). Elytra not upturned at apex; suture and intervals 5 and 7 costate on apical third; epipleurae irregularly serrate. Hind wings with CuA1 not forked at junction with MP3+4. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[237,291,700,722]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Legs:</emphasis>
Femora and tibiae expanded (fossorial); protibiae with posterior tooth at apex but not at midlength; tarsomere 4 weakly lobed. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[821,975,726,748]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Aedeagus with median lobe broadest near apex, weakly concave at apex (
<figureCitation box="[887,964,753,775]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[196,235,1249,1268]" captionTargetBox="[188,994,194,1226]" captionTargetId="figure-60@5.[186,994,194,1226]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 17–26. Dorsal view of aedeagi of Blaiseus spp. 17) B. bedeli Fleutiaux; 18) B. chiapasensis new species; 19) B. daklakensis new species; 20) B. fujianus new species; 21) B. guatemalensis new species; 22) B. laoensis new species; 23) B. malayensis new species; 24) B. mexicanus new species; 25) B. nothoafricanus new species; 26) B. zamoranoensis new species. d 5 dorsal apex of parameres; i 5 inner apex; v 5 ventral apex. Scale bar 5 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5496093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5496093/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
); parameres with ventral apices slightly longer than dorsal (setose) lobes. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[896,975,779,801]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Female:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,976,194,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,282,833,855]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was brought to my attention by a label, indicating that it belonged to genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FLEUTIAUX, A" authorityYear="1931" box="[372,454,860,881]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Blaiseus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[372,454,860,881]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Blaiseus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, attached to this specimen by Ms. Christine von Hayek. Evidence that this species is distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[674,821,886,907]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Blaiseus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daklakensis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[674,821,886,907]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">B. daklakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[830,949,886,908]" pageId="8" pageNumber="94" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is listed under that species. This is the only 
<taxonomicName box="[577,736,913,935]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Blaiseus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[577,659,913,934]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">Blaiseus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingCountry box="[880,945,913,935]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="94">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
